Congratulations to Kim Sheley of Backus, who was chosen as this year’s Pine River-Backus Teacher of the Year! 

It’s outstanding educators like Ms. Sheley who help hardworking Minnesota students succeed in and beyond the classroom. 

@PAL_EchoJournalhttp://www.pineandlakes.com/news/education/4363243-pine-river-backus-sheley-chosen-pr-b-teacher-year#.WiFyz0_KM1o.email …

This weekend in Grand Rapids, I had the honor of reuniting 88-year-old former U.S. Army Sergeant Gordon Oslin with the long-lost medals he earned during the Korean War. 

Thank you to Mr. Gordon's family, Oak Hill Assisted Living and @AmericanLegion! 
